  "prompt": "Where can I study at Stanford?",
  "response": "At Stanford University, you have a variety of options for studying, including:\n\n1. **Libraries**: Stanford has several libraries, including the Green Library, which is the main library on campus and offers a vast collection of books, journals, and study spaces. Other specialized libraries include the Martin Music Library and the Engineering Library.\n\n2. **Study Rooms**: There are numerous study rooms available in various buildings, including the libraries and academic buildings. Some are designed for group work, while others are more suited for quiet individual study.\n\n3. **Caf\u00e9s and Lounges**: Many caf\u00e9s on campus provide cozy environments for studying, such as the CoHo (the Coffee House) and the caf\u00e9 in the Graduate School of Business.\n\n4. **Classrooms and Lecture Halls**: If you have classes throughout the day, these spaces can also serve as study areas when not in use.\n\n5. **Academic Buildings**: Each academic department has its own facilities, including study lounges and common areas where students can study.\n\n6. **The Lathrop Library**: Located in the Cantor Arts Center, this library offers study spaces with a focus on arts and humanities.\n\n7. **Outdoor Spaces**: The Stanford campus features beautiful outdoor areas, such as the Main Quad and the Oval, where you can study in a more relaxed environment.\n\n8. **Residence Halls**: If you are a student living on campus, your residence hall often has study lounges or common areas.\n\nMake sure to check any specific access requirements, especially for some of the libraries and facilities that may have restrictions based on student status or time of day.",
